    ns1:inpersonHours "42 horas (32.3%)"@es ;
    ns1:numberOfCredits 5.0 ;
    ns1:otherInformation """The activities in the course will be organised on the moodle platform. All materials will be made available in this platform, and all assignments and other submissions will need to be done there.
The topics in which ontologies will be developed vary from edition to edition of the course, depending on the interests of students, but the most common ones are related to open data and transparency for cities (ODS11 and ODS16) and open data and transparency for universities (ODS4 an ODS16)."""@es ;
    ns1:periodEndingMonth "Enero"@es ;
    ns1:periodStartingMonth "Septiembre"@es ;
    ns1:teachingPeriod "2025-26" ;
    ns1:teachingPeriodMonths "Septiembre-Enero"@es ;
    ns1:totalHours "42 horas"@es ;
    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000367/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """The aim of this course is to discuss on the scientific, methodological and technological foundations that need to be considered when building ontologies. In particular, sessions in this course will cover:
The concepts of ontologies and ontology-based annotations in the context of the Semantic Web, the Web of Linked Data and Knowledge Graphs
Theoretical foundations in ontology development
Descriptions of some of the most widely-known ontologies and ontology catalogues
Ontology languages, such as RDF Schema and OWL, as well as vocabularies to represent taxonomies, such as SKOS
Methodologies, methods, techniques and tools used in ontology development, including requirements specification, planning, conceptualisation, reuse, reengineering, etc.
Ontology governance processes inside and across organisations
Relevant applications of ontologies.
Throughout the entire course open research problems will be presented and discussed collaboratively for each subtopic."""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/oscar.corcho%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/asunciondemaria.gomez%40upm.es>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/m.poveda%40upm.es>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/oscar.corcho%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Ingenieria Ontologica"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000367/2025-26/C1> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C1" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Ser capaces de aplicar técnicas de trabajo colaborativo en equipos multidisciplinares y liderazgo, así como utilizar métodos para asumir la responsabilidad de orientar y realizar trabajos científicos en el ámbito de la Inteligencia Artificial. (To be able to apply collaborative work techniques in multidisciplinary teams and leadership, as well as use methods to take responsibility for guiding and carrying out scientific work in the field of Artificial Intelligence). TIPO: Competencias."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000367/2025-26/C11> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C11" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Adquirir conocimientos científicos avanzados del campo de la informática que le permitan generar nuevas ideas dentro de una línea de investigación. (Acquire advanced scientific knowledge in the field of computer science that enables you to generate new ideas within a research line). TIPO: Competencias."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000367/2025-26/C14> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C14" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad de leer y comprender publicaciones dentro de su ámbito de estudio/investigación, así como su catalogación y valor científico. (Ability to read and understand publications within their area of study/research, as well as their categorization and"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000367/2025-26/C5> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "C5" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Saber desarrollar con autonomía e iniciativa proyectos sobre técnicas y aplicaciones avanzadas de Inteligencia Artificial, aplicando los principios fundamentales de la Inteligencia Artificial en cada etapa del proyecto. (To know how to autonomously and initiative"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000367/2025-26/K5> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "K5" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Conocer los métodos de representación del conocimiento y razonamiento aplicables al desarrollo de sistemas inteligentes en entornos centralizados y distribuidos. (To understand the methods of knowledge representation and reasoning applicable to the development of intelligent systems in centralized and distributed environaments). TIPO: Conocimientos o contenidos."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000367/2025-26/RA115> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA115" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Los resultados del aprendizaje correspondientes a esta asignatura han quedado definidos en el apartado de competencias de este documento, señalando los que corresponden a conocimientos, habilidades y competencias propiamente dichas."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000367/2025-26/S5> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "S5" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Almacenar conocimiento de forma que sea procesable por sistemas informáticos, posibilitando su reutilización en diferentes aplicaciones, y construir sistemas con capacidades de razonamiento para realizar de forma automática tareas tales como planificación o análisis de consistencia. (To store knowledge in a way that is processable by computer systems, enabling its reuse in different applications, and build systems with reasoning capabilities to automatically perform tasks such as planning or consistency analysis). TIPO: Habilidades o destrezas."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/103000367/2025-26/S8> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "S8" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Identificar áreas de aplicación en las que se puedan utilizar las técnicas y métodos de la Inteligencia Artificial y aplicar los mismos de manera adecuada. (To identify application areas where Artificial Intelligence techniques and methods can be used and apply them appropriately). TIPO: Habilidades o destrezas."@es .

